The trial for the beating death of University of Wyoming student Matthew Shepard has been postponed.
Russell Henderson and Aaron McKinney, both 21, face murder charges and the death penalty if convicted.
Authorities stated the attack was motivated by Shepard's sexual orientation.
Hate crime legislation is being pushed by Judy Shepard and others.
Henderson and McKinney posed as homosexuals to lure Shepard, leading to his tragic death.
The trial is expected to last five weeks.
Henderson's trial has been delayed due to a scheduling conflict.
The case has sparked calls for stronger bias crime laws.
